  <name>Audra</name>
  <summary>Native music player with Last.fm scrobbling</summary>

  <description>
    <p>
      Audra is a native music player for Linux built with GTK4 and
      libadwaita. It plays your local library and integrates with
      Last.fm for automatic scrobbling.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Local music library with cover art</li>
      <li>Shuffle-aware playback queue</li>
      <li>OS media controls (MPRIS)</li>
      <li>Automatic Last.fm scrobbling</li>
    </ul>
  </description>

  <launchable type="desktop-id">com.audra.player.desktop</launchable>

